SIMPLE: hank
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hank
<hw>Hank</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Dan.
<ets>hank</ets> handle, Sw. <ets>hank</ets> a band or tie, Icel.
<ets>hanki</ets> hasp, clasp, <ets>h⟦oum⟧nk</ets>, <ets>hangr</ets>,
hank, coil, skein, G. <ets>henkel</ets>, <ets>henk</ets>, handle; all
probably akin to E. <ets>hang</ets>. See <er>Hang</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A parcel consisting of two or more skeins of yarn or
thread tied together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rope or withe for fastening a gate.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hold; influence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the devil hath got such a <qex>hank</qex> over him.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Sanderson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A ring or eye of rope, wood, or
iron, attached to the edge of a sail and running on a stay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Wrestling)</fld> <def>A throw in which a wrestler
turns his left side to his opponent, twines his left leg about his
opponent's right leg from the inside, and throws him backward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hank</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hank
<hw>Hank</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[OE.
<ets>hanken</ets>.]</ety> <def>To fasten with a rope, as a gate.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To form into hanks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hanker</ent>⟦br⟧
